[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A healthcare care coordination assistant decomposes into ten logical stages: episode initiation and template instantiation, episode-state-store management, multi-system integration (read), stalled-episode detection, channel entry, input safety screening, identity-and-context loading, conversation handling with episode-grounded responses and tool-mediated actions, output safety screening with action approval gating, and care-team reporting with operational outcome correlation. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.8 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones (episode-of-care state machine ownership, multi-system integration governance, stalled-episode detection thresholds, action-tool ledger discipline, and cross-provider data-flow tracking).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── EPISODE INITIATION + TEMPLATE INSTANTIATION ──┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Episode initiated by clinical team or trigger event] │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Discharge from hospital (transitions-of-care)      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - New diagnosis requiring coordinated journey        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      (cancer, transplant evaluation, surgical referral) │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Multi-specialist referral chain initiated          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Maternity care episode opened                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Other institutionally-defined trigger              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Template instantiation]                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Episode template selected (per episode type)       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Template instantiated with patient-specific values │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      and dependencies                                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Expected steps, expected timelines, escalation     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      thresholds, communication touchpoints              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Episode signed by care team                        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Patient consented to coordination assistance       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: active episode record; episode state         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    machine initialized]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
