[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Episode-of-care state machine with operational-leadership ownership.** Each episode type has a structured state machine, owned by the appropriate operational leadership (oncology nurse navigation for oncology coordination, transitions-of-care nursing leadership for post-discharge, surgical nursing leadership for perioperative coordination, etc.), reviewed before adoption, reviewed annually, and re-reviewed when material updates are made.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-system integration governance with named ownership per system.** Each integration partner (EHR, scheduling, prior-auth, lab, imaging, pharmacy, home health, payer, external HIE) has named operational ownership, integration-pattern documentation, error-handling policies, and audit-trail requirements.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Stalled-episode detection thresholds with operational tuning.** Detection thresholds are episode-specific and institution-specific; tuning is multi-quarter operational discipline driven by care-team feedback. Thresholds are not chosen by the LLM.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Action-tool ledger discipline as architectural primitive.** Every state-changing action is durable-recorded with patient-confirmation evidence, integrated-system request and response, outcome, and reversibility classification. The ledger is the audit primitive that lets the institution reconstruct what the assistant did.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-provider data-flow tracking.** Artifacts flowing across organizational boundaries are tracked through whatever path is available. Tracking is operational primitive, with explicit handling for the heterogeneous interoperability surface.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Continuous frustration detection.** Patient frustration is a routine emotional context in care-coordination conversations. The assistant detects frustration cues and responds with action and validation, not explanation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Care-team reporting and operational outcome correlation as first-class.** Real-time alerts, daily worklists, weekly digests, and operational outcome correlation are part of production scope, not phase-2 enhancements.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement rate, stalled-episode rate, action-success rate, time-to-resolution, and patient satisfaction vary by language, channel, episode type, age cohort, sex, and social-determinant flags. Per-cohort dashboards are reviewed by clinical leadership, operations, and patient experience.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When integrated systems are unreachable, the assistant degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I am having trouble checking on that right now; for anything urgent please contact your care team at [number]."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
